<item>
            <title>[LU-4146] Ability to selectively stop testing</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4146</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Each patch takes ~12h to pass today,&lt;br/&gt;
     and while this is already a long time, it would be nice to enable even&lt;br/&gt;
     more tests for each patch.  To make this reasonable, patches should test&lt;br/&gt;
     in several stages, and only continue if they don&apos;t fail too many tests.&lt;br/&gt;
     Ideally, we could restart the stages separately, to avoid huge delays in&lt;br/&gt;
     case of some small failure.  Posting the results to Maloo incrementally&lt;br/&gt;
     (i.e. after every test script completes) would also be useful.  For this&lt;br/&gt;
     to be useful it would be great to avoid repeated node provisioning for&lt;br/&gt;
     each test. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
